<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 7:56PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Floyd,
northeastern Polk and southwestern Bartow Counties through 830 PM
EDT...
At 756 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Taylorsville, or 12
miles southeast of Rome, moving west at 10 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rome, Rockmart, Euharlee, Aragon, Taylorsville, Seney, Lindale and
Stilesboro.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
